Syrian Press Center
fields.description_en: The Syrian Press Center is a non-governmental independent media organisation based in Idlib and Hamah provinces with reporters throughout Syria.  Unaffiliated to any political party or movement, their mission is to provide neutral and objective reporting on the situation in Syria while defending freedom of expression. They also raise awareness of the risks facing journalists and media activists working in Syria and push to defend their rights and professional circumstances.  The Syrian Press Center also provides media training inside Syria in areas such as basic journalism skills, TV and documentary production, the analysis of photo and video materials, and investigative reporting.

fields.international_instrument_notes: Some commentators and institutions have labeled barrel bombs as incendiary devices, which are banned for use against populated civilian areas under the terms of the UN Convention on Prohibitions or Restrictions on the Use of Certain Conventional Weapons. Human Rights Watch has insisted that the employment of these weapons constitutes a war crime. According to Victoria Nuland, of the United States Department of State, barrel bombs are "incendiary bombs which contain flammable material that can be like napalm" or can be packed with nails and launched from the air or from a launche
fields.description: The video shows a helicopter dropping a barrel bomb on civilian areas in Daraa - Inkhil.
